Memoire Studio notices

Studio interface references and adapted components:

- Hermes WebUI (MIT): https://github.com/nesquena/hermes-webui
  Memoire Studio adapts the transcript-first, calm console interaction pattern and
  three-pane workbench organization from the public Hermes WebUI project.

- Hermes Agent (MIT): https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent
  Memoire Studio adapts runtime ideas around agent sessions, normalized events,
  approval-oriented supervision, and local execution boundaries from the public
  Hermes Agent project.

- Warp UI framework (MIT pieces only): https://github.com/warpdotdev/Warp
  Memoire Studio may reference or adapt MIT-licensed Warp UI framework ideas from
  warpui_core and warpui. Warp AGPL application/client code is not copied.

Product references:

- Warp terminal block behavior is used as a product reference for command blocks,
  grouped output, and terminal-native workflows. AGPL application/client code is
  excluded from this repository unless a future licensing decision explicitly
  changes that boundary.

Optional video adapters:

- Remotion: https://www.remotion.dev/
  Memoire creates filesystem-first video project scaffolds that can be previewed
  or rendered with Remotion when it is installed by the user.

- HyperFrames: https://github.com/heygen-com/hyperframes
  Memoire treats HyperFrames as an optional adapter for open design-to-video
  workflows; it is not bundled as a hard dependency.
